{"id":"chat4","text":"There is an existing channel you are not in. How do you find and join it?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click Browse Channels to see existing channels and join one","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"You cannot join a channel — an admin has to add you"},{"id":"c","text":"Search for it in the app's main search bar at the top"},{"id":"d","text":"Create a new channel with the same name"}],"explanation":"Browse Channels shows you channels you're not in yet so you can find one and join it."},{"id":"chat5","text":"How do you send a message you have typed?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Press Enter — the message sends right away","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Press Shift+Enter to send"},{"id":"c","text":"Click outside the message box"},{"id":"d","text":"Wait 5 seconds for it to send by itself"}],"explanation":"Press Enter to send. The message box is a single line, so there's no line break with Shift+Enter — Enter always sends, and the message goes out right away."},{"id":"chat6","text":"You want to reply to one message without cluttering the main conversation. What do you use?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Reply in thread — it opens a side panel and keeps that back-and-forth together","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Start a new direct message with everyone in the channel"},{"id":"c","text":"Edit the original message to add your reply"},{"id":"d","text":"Quote the message in a new channel"}],"explanation":"Reply in thread opens a side panel for that message. A message with replies shows a replies link that reopens the thread, keeping side conversations out of the main flow."},{"id":"chat7","text":"A message includes a link to a job. What happens when that link appears in the conversation?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It shows as plain text you have to copy and paste into the address bar"},{"id":"b","text":"It appears as a tappable colored label that opens the job's details","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It downloads the job as a file"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing — links to records don't work anywhere in chat"}],"explanation":"Links to records — a job, part, purchase order, sales order, quote, and more — appear as tappable colored labels that open that record's details. Note: the message box is a plain text box today, so typing @ doesn't open a picker; these links arrive on messages that come from elsewhere in the app."},{"id":"chat8","text":"Who can post in a read-only broadcast (announcement) channel?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Anyone who is in the channel"},{"id":"b","text":"Only admins and managers","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only the person who created the channel"},{"id":"d","text":"No one — broadcast channels are just archives"}],"explanation":"Broadcast channels are read-only: only admins and managers can post. Everyone else reads the announcements but can't reply in the channel."},{"id":"chat9","text":"Where does an admin go to write and send a company announcement, and what can they control?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"From the chat box — they type the announcement straight into a channel message"},{"id":"b","text":"From the Admin area — choosing who it reaches (whole company, a department, or specific teams), its importance, whether people must confirm they read it, and an expiry date","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Anywhere — any user can post an announcement from any direct message"},{"id":"d","text":"From a compose tab in the top-bar notifications panel"}],"explanation":"Announcements are written from the Admin area, not from chat. Chat is where you receive and read them. From Admin, an admin or manager chooses who it reaches (whole company, a department, or specific teams), its importance (Info, Warning, or Critical), whether people must confirm they read it, an optional expiry date, and can reuse templates."},{"id":"chat10","text":"A channel is very busy and the alerts are distracting, but you still need to stay in it. What do you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Leave the channel"},{"id":"b","text":"Mute the channel from its row to turn off alerts while staying a member","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Delete all the messages"},{"id":"d","text":"Block the other members"}],"explanation":"Mute turns off a channel's alerts without taking you out of it. A muted channel shows a crossed-out bell; you're still a member and can still read it."},{"id":"chat11","text":"How do messages get marked as read, and what does the top-bar number show?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"You click 'Mark as read' on each message; the number shows whether you're online"},{"id":"b","text":"Opening a conversation marks its messages read; the top-bar number shows your total unread across all chats and channels","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Messages read themselves after 10 seconds; the number shows how many channels you have"},{"id":"d","text":"You scroll to the bottom; the number shows how many people are online"}],"explanation":"Opening a chat or channel marks its messages read. The chat icon in the top bar shows your total unread across every conversation and updates the moment new messages arrive."},{"id":"chat12","text":"What does a channel member's role (Member, Admin, or Owner) decide?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Nothing — the roles are just labels"},{"id":"b","text":"Member reads and posts; Admin can edit and manage the channel; Owner has full control including deleting it","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The color of the member's initials"},{"id":"d","text":"How many messages the member can send per day"}],"explanation":"Roles decide what each person can do: a Member reads and posts, an Admin can rename, edit, and manage the channel, and an Owner has full control including deleting the channel."},{"id":"chat13","text":"You want to keep chat visible on a second monitor while you work in the app. What do you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Open the slide-out chat and click Open in window to move chat into its own window","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Make the browser window big so chat fills the whole screen"},{"id":"c","text":"You can't — chat has to stay inside the app"},{"id":"d","text":"Bookmark the chat page and refresh it every few minutes"}],"explanation":"From the slide-out chat, Open in window moves chat into its own window you can put on a second monitor. While it's open, the panel shows a note that chat is in a separate window plus a Focus window button, and conversations you click in the panel open in that window. Close the window to go back to the slide-out."}]}"""
