            Tags = """["chat","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## The Kinds of Channels\n\nThere are several kinds of channels, but you only ever *create* two of them yourself:\n\n- **Direct message** — a private one-on-one chat. It's made for you when you start a chat with someone; it never shows up in the new-channel window.\n- **Group** — the normal kind you make yourself: a shared channel for a topic.\n- **Open** — the other kind you can make. **Only open channels can be found and joined by others.** Use an open channel when you want people to discover it and join on their own.\n- **Team** — set up automatically for a team (one per team) and grouped under that team's heading. You don't make these yourself.\n- **Department** — a channel for a department, set up by the app rather than the new-channel window.\n- **System** — set up automatically for built-in purposes; you can't leave these.\n- **Broadcast** — a read-only announcement channel; only admins and managers can post.\n\nWhen you make a new channel, you can only choose **Group** or **Open** — every other kind is set up by the app.\n\n## Who Can Do What in a Channel\n\nEach person in a channel is a Member, an Admin, or the Owner. What you can do in a channel's settings depends on that role, **not** on your company-wide admin or manager role:\n\n- **Member** — read and post, mute their own alerts, and leave. A Member can't edit the channel; only channel admins and owners can change its settings.\n- **Admin** — everything a Member can do, plus rename and edit the channel and manage who's in it.\n- **Owner** — full control, including deleting the channel.\n\nLeaving works the same for everyone: you can't leave a direct message, a system channel, or a broadcast channel, no matter your role. And you can only join open channels.\n\n## What You Can Attach (and the 10 MB Limit)\n\nThe file types you can attach are the same everywhere in chat:\n\nPDFs, common images (JPG, PNG, GIF), office documents (Word, Excel), plain text and spreadsheet files (TXT, CSV), and the three common engineering-drawing formats (STEP, STL, DXF).\n\nThere's a hard size limit: a file over **10 MB** is turned away before it uploads. Today that happens quietly, with no error message. Once a file uploads, it goes out with your next message.\n\n## Writing Announcements (for Admins)\n\nAnnouncements are separate from chat — chat only *receives and shows* them. You write them in the **Admin** area, and that area can be turned on or off separately from chat. Who can do what:\n\n- **List, create, edit, delete, and send announcements** — admins and managers.\n- **Manage templates** — admins and managers can view them, but only admins can create or delete a template.\n- **Confirm you've read one** — anyone who's signed in.\n\nWhen writing an announcement you set:\n\n- **Importance** — Info, Warning, or Critical.\n- **Who it reaches** — the whole company, one department, or specific teams (and there are team-lead options too).\n- **Must confirm** — whether readers have to confirm they've read it.\n- **Expiry** — an optional date when it goes away on its own.\n- **Templates** — reusable starting points that can pre-fill the importance, who it reaches, and whether confirmation is required.\n\nAnnouncements arrive the moment they're sent, showing up in chat and in read-only broadcast channels.\n\n## Turning Chat On or Off\n\nAn admin can turn the whole chat feature on or off for your company. When it's off, chat goes dark — the panel and the top-bar icon stop working. Announcements are controlled separately, so your company can run announcements without chat, or chat without announcements.","sections":[]}"""
        });

